Backend:
- Node.js
- Express.js (v5)
- TypeScript
- Prisma (ORM) + @prisma/adapter-pg (native PostgreSQL driver)
- Supabase (managed PostgreSQL host)
- Zod (server-side validation & schema parsing)
- JWT (dual-token: access token 15min + refresh token 30d)
- bcrypt (password hashing, salt factor 10)
- Nodemailer (transactional email via SMTP/STARTTLS)
- express-rate-limit (DDoS protection, 500 req/15min)
- cors
- dotenv
- nodemon / tsx / ts-node (dev tooling)
- Docker (multi-stage build containerisation)
- Docker Compose (environment & port management)
- Postman (API endpoint testing)

Authentication:
    Login — verifies credentials, issues access + refresh token
    Logout — revokes refresh token from database
    Refresh — issues new access token using valid refresh token
    withAuth middleware — applied to all protected endpoints
    Ownership checks — in place for all routes with a userId param
    req.user — attached in withAuth, typed via express.d.ts
    Email verification — 6-digit token, expires 10 minutes, sent on sign-up
    Password reset — 6-digit token flow, expires 10 minutes

Frontend:
- React Native (v0.81)
- React (v19)
- Expo (v54)
- expo-router
- React Navigation (native-stack, bottom-tabs, material-top-tabs)
- TanStack React Query (server state & caching)
- Axios (HTTP client)
- Zod (client-side form validation)
- AsyncStorage (token persistence)
- react-native-paper (UI component library)
- react-native-pager-view
- expo-image-picker (image selection)
- expo-file-system
- @expo/vector-icons
- TypeScript

Database:
- PostgreSQL (hosted on Supabase)
- Prisma schema (12 models: User, Task, Event, TaskAssignment, EventAssignment, Reviews, Transactions, Conversation, Message, Hashtags, EmailVerificationToken, RefreshToken)
- Prisma enums: TaskTypes, EventTypes, Status, ApplicationStatus, Rating, TransactionType

Infrastructure & Tooling:
- Docker + Docker Compose (backend containerisation)
- GitHub (version control, branching strategy: main / dev / feature branches)
- Postman (API testing)
